<HEADLINE>
President declares Friday a day of mourning for Pope John Paul II
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
BLANTYRE, Malawi
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
President Bingu wa Mutharika declared Friday a national day of mourning for the
late Pope John Paul II, allowing the faithful to attend special
services.
</P>
<P>
All government offices, banks and businesses closed Friday, the day of the
pope's funeral at the Vatican.
</P>
<P>
Malawi has more than 4 million Roman Catholics, making it the largest church in
the southern African country.
</P>
<P>
The president, a Roman Catholic, attended a special mass in the capital,
Lilongwe, where he praised John Paul as a man of peace and love.
</P>
